div.p:
John repeatedly (often towards the end of an already rather lengthy
chapter) asserts that he only gives a short account and omits much so as
to prevent an exaggerate length of his work; see, for instance,
EH
                        3.1.18.o; 3.1.21.e;
3.1.30.e; 3.2.1.a; 3.2.4.d;
3.2.7.i; 3.2.15.g; 3.4.7;
3.4.13; 3.4.45; 3.4.48;
3.4.53; 3.4.61
                        (van Ginkel 1995, 184).

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.3 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:293.b.34–294.b.22; 4:337.a.38–338.b.13: summary of the chapter in EH;
see 3.1.9.a

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.3 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:296.a.8–13; 4:339.b.9–12: summary of parts of the chapter in EH;
see 3.1.11.c and 3.1.11.g

The Greek loanword ܐ̣ܝܪܛܝܘܢ “hierateion”
(ἱερατεῖον) is only rarely attested in Syriac Butts 2016a, 75; 
                        Brockelmann 1928, 130.

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.5 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:297.a.16–26; 4:339.b.41–340.a.4: summary of the chapter in EH;
see 3.1.15.a

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.5 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:298.a.35–299.a.11; 4:340.a.40–341.b.6: summary of the chapter in EH;
see 3.1.18.a

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.6 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:301.a.4–5; 4:342.a.1–2: summary of parts of the chapter in EH;
see 2.1.23.a

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.6 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:303.a.19–24; 4:343.b.17–21: summary of the chapter in EH;
see3.1.30.e

                     Michael the Syrian,
Chronicle 10.6 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:300.a.24–27; 4:341.b.33–36 and 10.7 Chabot 1899–1910, 2:306.a.6–13; 4:344.a.44–345.b.5: summary of the chapter in EH;
see 3.1.31.e

